Four-year-old Nina Gomes retrieves trash from the ocean in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. 

Nina has recently been named as the youngest 'Green Agent' by the Municipal Urban Cleaning Company. She says she does it because 'otherwise fish and turtles will die.' Eleven million tons of plastic are discarded into the ocean every year, according to the United Nations Environment Programme. 

#environment #ocean #pollution #conservation #brazil 

REUTERS/Pilar Olivares

Muslim pilgrims perform Tawaf by circling the Kaaba during the annual Hajj pilgrimage, in the holy city of Mecca, Saudi Arabia. 

Only 60,000 fully vaccinated citizens and residents are allowed to take part this year, due to ongoing coronavirus restrictions. Pre-pandemic, the ritual would regularly see crowds of up to 2.5 million people. 

#islam #religion #worship #pilgrimage #hajj
